      {
        "id": "TILE1hhHkLiAcfIg",
        "content": {
          "type": "Text",
          "format": "html",
          "text": [
            "<p><strong>Summarize (Orchestrating the Discussion)</strong></p><p><em>Discussing Solutions and Strategies </em></p><p>Discuss Baruti&#x27;s science grades. Ask students to analyze the percentages in the grades.</p>"
          ]
        }
      },
      {
        "id": "TILEKcqDryoCE4M1",
        "content": {
          "type": "Text",
          "format": "html",
          "text": [
            "<p><strong>Suggested Questions </strong></p><ul><li>Baruti only missed 1 point on each assignment. Does that make all of his grades the same? </li></ul>"
          ]
        }
      },
      {
        "id": "TILEsTGkpR30JJKf",
        "display": "teacher",
        "content": {
          "type": "Text",
          "format": "html",
          "text": [
            "<p>No. He only missed 1 point, but the number of points changes, so that changes his grade from assignment to assignment. </p>"
          ]
        }
      },
      {
        "id": "dKCc4bMocCMCZRdt",
        "title": "Text 17",
        "content": {
          "type": "Text",
          "format": "html",
          "text": [
            "<ul><li>Which of the assignments has the lowest percentage grade? </li></ul>"
          ]
        }
      },
      {
        "id": "dgkbCToe3Vr5PgSj",
        "title": "Text 18",
        "display": "teacher",
        "content": {
          "type": "Text",
          "format": "html",
          "text": [
            "<p>Test. 24 points out of 25 points is equivalent to 96 points out of 100, or 96%.</p>"
          ]
        }
      },
      {
        "id": "TILE3qhBp8NrOMqw",
        "content": {
          "type": "Text",
          "format": "html",
          "text": [
            "<ul><li>Which of the assignments has the lowest percentage grade? </li></ul>"
          ]
        }
      },
      {
        "id": "TILE2rEzCmegS0vI",
        "display": "teacher",
        "content": {
          "type": "Text",
          "format": "html",
          "text": [
            "<p>Homework #1. 1 point out of 2 points is equivalent to 50 points out of 100 points, or 50%.</p>"
          ]
        }
      },
      {
        "id": "K0FPX8qcbkzmvlZ2",
        "title": "Text 19",
        "content": {
          "type": "Text",
          "format": "html",
          "text": [
            "<ul><li>Baruti missed 1 point on the Test and 1 point on Homework #1. Why is there such a difference in the percentages? </li></ul>"
          ]
        }
      },
      {
        "id": "r3A3oJmf3svi8b_H",
        "title": "Text 24",
        "display": "teacher",
        "content": {
          "type": "Text",
          "format": "html",
          "text": [
            "<p>In the test, each point is worth 4% of the grade. In the homework assignment, each point is worth 50% of the grade. So the homework points have more influence on the percentage grade.</p>"
          ]
        }
      },
      {
        "id": "cBaUGPo3Ko5WrI_P",
        "title": "Text 20",
        "content": {
          "type": "Text",
          "format": "html",
          "text": [
            "<p>This idea can be illustrated graphically using <strong>Teaching Aid 4.4A: Homework and Test Points</strong>. (Portrayal) Students might express the homework points as having more &quot;weight&quot; or more percentage. If we remove 1 point from the Homework 1, we lose much of the percentage. If we remove 1 point from the Test, we don&#x27;t lose as much percentage. </p>"
          ]
        }
      },
